cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

The paper discusses the use of Convolutional Networks (ConvNets) for visual recognition tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also investigates factors affecting the transferability of ConvNet representations, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The optimization of these factors involves adjusting the architecture and training data distribution of the ConvNet, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the ConvNet representations on various visual recognition tasks, which could be considered natural language processing (cs.CL) since some of the tasks involve text recognition.
